First of all, why, oh why, do you want me to start in on something that has nothing to do with me? If you'll note, I really don't care about the elemental planes discussion, because, frankly, it doesn't concern me. There's a level of &quot;eh, who the fuck cares&quot; and an equal part &quot;the forum will be there when it is all done, one way or another&quot;. <br>
<br>
Again, I suspect that because Rigg is my guildmate, you expect me to have some leash on him. <br>
<br>
1. Public forum<br>
2. Individual poster<br>
3. Personal thoughts<br>
<br>
Sounds like he's got the ability to say whatever he wants. Funny, just like I do. I don't know how other guilds work, but I wouldn't be in a guild for long if I wasn't allowed to disagree with my guild leader, and he/she told me I couldn't OR ELSE. (I know Rigg; he is arguing because he thinks he is right, and like I said before, since it was asked, I do happen to agree with at least some of the argument about making/expanding the 'them' and 'us' on this server, and that, not any guild going rogue, but that, is a bigger threat to the RTA P&amp;P than anything else. I digress.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
We all know that Rigg only reads what he wants, and picks out pieces of posts, while totatlly ignoring other points and posts.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
And you're... frustrated with that? Angry about that? Annoyed even?<br>
<br>
I suggest you flame him. It's done wonders for my frustrations with Seer. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
It's not your views on a subject, it's how you treat the posters of those subject.<br>
<br>
You berate Seer for her views and beliefs on Hate, which she has every right to have regardless of what *you* think she should believe.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, and I think I said this before, but I'll say it again. <br>
<br>
I was/am berating seer for not seeming to *read* the words on the screen before she replied. You disagree, regardless of what *I* think you should believe. However, when you say &quot;What about point A?&quot; and I say &quot;Here's the reason, here's how the rules cover it&quot; you don't say &quot;What about point A? What about point A?! WHAT ABOUT POINT A?!?&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, maybe sometimes you do. But I like you. Oh, and, yes, that's a valid answer. We are, in fact, on the ... (say it with me now) FLAME FORUM!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Yet you allow Rigorre to post as he does, without a murmur. You don't call him a &quot;fuckstick&quot; or a &quot;jerkweed&quot; or any of the other colorful things you did Seer. <br>
<br>
That's why I don't think you're &quot;fair&quot;. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Ah! I see. I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>allow</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> him to post, and that's not fair to you. <br>
<br>
Now, I'm going to read this in the way I *think* you intend it, not the way it, in fact, sounds. Keeping that in mind, here goes:<br>
<br>
You, and all other posters who have that big an issue with Rigg, have a keyboard, a brain, and the ability to hopefully use both at the same time. If you think Rigg deserves a written barrage, by all means, start a thread. Correct me if I'm wrong, but that's what the flame forum is about, right? You take a person, subject, or event, that you think sucks, and blast into it. <br>
<br>
Don't get mad at me because I'm good at it, or I have creative ways to say that someone is a moron. The pictures paint a thousand words, sort of thing... do you flame off Jurr when he posts &quot;STFU&quot; pictures? No? <br>
<br>
Now who's not fair?<br>
<br>
If your frustration with Rigg is indeed as great as mine was with Seer, to the point of not being able to remain at least partially civil in the general forum (which, you'll remember, the post about the elemental planes is in, despite several occasions that it warrented moving to flames...), than by all means, start a thread, complain about him. <br>
<br>
I don't have any complaints, because, you'll notice, I'm not trying to change his mind. I know what he thinks, I think (by and large) that he's wrong, and the rest of it, doesn't really bother me, since it has nothing to do with me. <br>
<br>
Do you mean to suggest that before I am 'allowed' to flame someone, I must either a) take everyone who posts on the flame boards into consideration in my flames, or b) talk about everyone who is currently saying things that I disagree with? <br>
<br>
Honestly, if I was anyone else saying what I'm saying about Seer, you wouldn't have brought Rigg into this conversation, all other things equal. You think, however, because I'm his guild leader, that saying &quot;well, riggs being stubborn and stupid, why not flame him&quot; will put me on the defensive. <br>
<br>
Yeah, no. Just because I know him, and like him, and happen to know for a level fact that he's not arguing for the sake of argument, and he's actually right about the way the forum was created versus how it should have been created, etc etc, does not give you the ability to tell me who and how I flame. <br>
<br>
Did I miss the memo that all flames now must be proportionate to *everyone* before one can break out the gas and matches?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Karadin, versus Rogg, versus Nycah.<br>
C'mon dorf, do it for us. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think some of the confusion comes in the distinction between 'fair' and 'impartial'. <br>
<br>
It is actually a fair assessment to say that Seer missed the repeated explanations on the general thread. It is also fair to say that she replied as if the words before had not been written. I flamed her for that (not, you'll note again, because of what she believed).<br>
<br>
Is it impartial to flame only one person at a time? Probably not. <br>
<br>
Is that anything that should be thrown at me specifically as someone who's started a flame about someone else? <br>
<br>
Hrm, well, if we want to be 'fair', we'd have to bitch out everyone who's ever started a thread on this forum...<br>
<br>
*cough*<br>
<br>
Sorry Jurr, I was going for a short post, didn't work out that way. <br>
<br>
-Rogg<br>
